TI - Crystal structure of the <p1  pair=1 >  <prot>  BMP - 2 </prot>  </p1>  - <p2  pair=1 >  <prot>  BRIA </prot>  </p2>  ectodomain complex .
PG - 492 - 6 AB - Bone morphogenetic proteins ( BMPs ) belong to the large <prot>  transforming growth factor - beta </prot>  ( <prot>  TGF - beta </prot>  ) superfamily of multifunctional cytokines .
 <prot> BMP - 2 </prot>  can induce ectopic bone and cartilage formation in adult vertebrates and is involved in central steps in early embryonal development in animals .
Signaling by these cytokines requires binding of two types of transmembrane serine / threonine receptor kinase chains classified as type I and type II .
Here we report the crystal structure of human dimeric <p1  pair=2 >  <p1  pair=3 >  <p1  pair=4 >  <p2  pair=2 >  <prot>  BMP - 2 </prot>  </p2>  </p1>  </p1>  </p1>  in complex with two high affinity <p2  pair=3 >  <prot>  <prot>  BMP receptor IA </prot>  extracellular domain </prot>  </p2>  ( <p2  pair=4 >  <prot>  BRIAec </prot>  </p2>  ) .
The receptor chains bind to the ' wrist ' epitopes of the <p1  pair=5 >  <p2  pair=5 >  <prot>  BMP - 2 </prot>  </p2>  </p1>  dimer and contact both <prot>  BMP - 2 </prot>  monomers .
No contacts exist between the receptor domains .
The model reveals the structural basis for discrimination between type I and type II receptors and the variability of receptor - ligand interactions that is seen in BMP - <prot>  TGF - beta </prot>  systems .
AD - Physiologische Chemie II , Biozentrum der Universitat Wurzburg , Germany .
